
.row.blurb
  .col
    %h4 Your own wiki in seconds
    %p
      Get your own powerful, extensible, personal wiki in seconds with no installation
      required. Make it private, public, or show it off in the
      #{link_to('Tiddlyhost Hub', '/hub')}.

  .col
    %h4 Powered by TiddlyWiki
    %p

      Tiddlyhost is powered by #{link_to 'TiddlyWiki', 'https://tiddlywiki.com/'}
      the revolutionary open source JavaScript wiki. It also supports the new
      superlight #{link_to 'Feather Wiki', 'https://feather.wiki/'} and the
      old-school original #{link_to 'TiddlyWiki Classic', 'https://classic.tiddlywiki.com/'}.

  .col
    %h4 From the creator of Tiddlyspot
    %p
      Tiddlyhost is the secure, modern, reliable successor to Tiddlyspot, and its
      code is #{link_to 'open source', 'https://github.com/simonbaird/tiddlyhost'}.
      Find out more at the #{link_to 'FAQ', 'https://github.com/simonbaird/tiddlyhost/wiki/FAQ'}
      or the #{link_to 'About', '/about'} page.

.jumbotron
  %h3 Get started now
  =link_to new_user_registration_path, class: 'btn btn-lg btn-primary' do
    Sign up
  %span or
  =link_to new_user_session_path, class: 'btn btn-lg btn-primary' do
    Log in
